Thus $G / N$ exists for ''all'' subgroups of $G$.
Let $X = x N, Y = y N$ where $x, y \in G$.
From the definition of coset product:

X Y = \paren {x N} \paren {y N}
\paren {x y N}
\paren {y x N}
