From Projection is Surjection, $\pr_1$ and $\pr_2$ are surjections.
We now need to show they are homomorphisms.
Let $s, t \in \struct {S, \circ}$ where $s = \tuple {s_1, s_2}$ and $t = \tuple {t_1, t_2$.
Then:

\map {\pr_1} {s \circ t} = \map {\pr_1} {\tuple {s_1, s_2} \circ \tuple {t_1, t_2} }
\map {\pr_1} {\tuple {s_1 \circ_1 t_1, s_2 \circ_2 t_2} }
s_1 \circ_j t_1
\map {\pr_1} s \circ_1 \map {\pr_1} t

\map {\pr_2} {s \circ t} = \map {\pr_2} {\tuple {s_1, s_2} \circ \tuple {t_1, t_2} }
\map {\pr_2} {\tuple {s_1 \circ_1 t_1, s_2 \circ_2 t_2} }
s_2 \circ_j t_2
\map {\pr_2} s \circ_2 \map {\pr_2} t

Thus the morphism property is demonstrated for both $\pr_1$ and $\pr_2$.

